“The Botched Hunt for the Gilgo Beach Killer“ for the New York Times Magazine, written by @bobkolker 

I remember this news so vividly from when I was in my senior year at Pratt. The bodies of several women had been found on a stretch of Ocean Parkway - the same stretch that my best friend at school could see in the distance from the backyard of his childhood home. Bobby and I would talk about the various theories and speculation on Long Island and we both read Bob Kolker’s book Lost Girls, which we found particularly well-researched because of the emphasis and care given to exploring the lives of the women who were found. This summer’s arrest was a shock to everyone familiar with the case and so many are relieved to see a man face trial. The time I spent out on Ocean Parkway over the course of several days and nights, looking at the photographs of Maureen Brainard-Barnes, Megan Waterman, Amber Costello, and Melissa Barthelemy and feeling the isolation of that place will stick with me for a long time. I highly recommend a read or listen in the app.

Thanks to Coralie and the NYTM, & the Walsh family. 🌸

2. Ocean Parkway at dusk 3. Site where Melissa Barthelemy’s body was found 4. Ocean Parkway after sunset 5. Site where Megan Waterman’s body was found 6. Ocean Parkway at night 7.Site where Maureen Brainard-Barnes’ body was found
